      passage: `<p>Earlier work indicates that honeybee pollination accounts for as much as 10 percent of all the Chinese cabbage produced in a given season. Researchers now want to learn how heavily cucumber production, in turn, depends on honeybees. In the first phase of their study, they covered some cucumber plants with screens so that no insects could pollinate them; those covered plants yielded 40 to 90 percent less than the plants that had been pollinated normally. The researchers caution, though, that this first phase on its own could not reveal how much of that gap comes specifically from keeping honeybees away.</p>`,
