      passage: `<p>Scientists have built a model to forecast how growing human activity will change the sizes of future mammal populations in US national forests. Unfortunately, for large forests the model overshoots its predictions for large-mammal populations, and for small forests it overshoots its predictions for small-mammal populations. Ashland Ridge National Forest, a Montana forest that spans well over 3 million acres, plainly counts as large. Used to gauge the effect of rising human activity on this particular forest a decade from now, the model would therefore likely ______</p>`,
